                        "steps":  [
                                      "Start the yellow rice first and cook it according to the packet directions, since it will usually take longer than the taco filling. If using microwave yellow rice, wait until the taco meat is almost done.",
                                      "Set out the toppings before cooking the beef: shredded cheese, lettuce, sour cream, salsa or tomatoes, and avocado or guacamole if using. Taco night works best when the toppings are ready before the shells are hot.",
                                      "Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the ground beef and cook for 5 to 7 minutes, breaking it into small crumbles, until no pink remains.",
                                      "Drain excess fat if the skillet looks greasy. Leave a little moisture and browned flavor in the pan so the seasoning can coat the meat well.",
                                      "Add the taco kit seasoning and the amount of water called for on the box, usually about 2/3 to 3/4 cup. Stir well, bring to a bubble, then reduce the heat.",
                                      "Simmer the beef for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring often, until the sauce thickens and the beef looks glossy instead of watery.",
                                      "Warm the hard shells and soft tortillas according to the taco kit directions. Keep an eye on hard shells because they can go from warm to cracked or overbrowned quickly.",
                                      "Transfer the taco meat to a serving bowl and set out the shells, tortillas, yellow rice, cheese, lettuce, sour cream, taco sauce, and any optional toppings.",
                                      "Let everyone build their own tacos, soft tacos, rice bowls, or deconstructed plates. For kids, start with plain beef, cheese, and rice, then add lettuce, sauce, or sour cream only if they want it."
                                  ],
